HWLldpPortId.name: HWLldpPortId
HWLldpPortId.description: This TC describes the format of a port identifier string. Objects of this type are always used with an associated LldpPortIdSubtype object, which identifies the format of the particular LldpPortId object instance. If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'interfaceAlias(1)', then the octet string identifies a particular instance of the ifAlias object (defined in IETF RFC 2863). If the particular ifAlias object does not contain any values, another port identifier type should be used. If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'portComponent(2)', then the octet string identifies a particular instance of the entPhysicalAlias object (defined in IETF RFC 2737) for a port or backplane component. If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'macAddress(3)', then this string identifies a particular unicast source address (encoded in network byte order and IEEE 802.3 canonical bit order) associated with the port (IEEE Std 802-2001). If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'networkAddress(4)', then this string identifies a network address associated with the port. The first octet contains the IANA AddressFamilyNumbers enumeration value for the specific address type, and octets 2 through N contain the networkAddress address value in network byte order. If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'interfaceName(5)', then the octet string identifies a particular instance of the ifName object (defined in IETF RFC 2863). If the particular ifName object does not contain any values, another port identifier type should be used. If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'agentCircuitId(6)', then this string identifies a agent-local identifier of the circuit (defined in RFC 3046). If the associated LldpPortIdSubtype object has a value of 'local(7)', then this string identifies a locally assigned port ID.

nqaAdminCtrlOwnerIndex.name: nqaAdminCtrlOwnerIndex
nqaAdminCtrlOwnerIndex.description: To facilitate the provisioning of access control by a security administrator using the View-Based Access Control Model for tables in which multiple users may need to independently create or modify entries, the initial index is used as an 'ownerindex'. When used in conjunction with such a security policy all entries in the table belonging to a particular user (or group) will have the same value for this initial index. For a given user's entries in a particular table, the object identifiers for the information in these entries will have the same subidentifiers (except for the 'column' subidentifier) up to the end of the encoded owner index.

nqaAdminCtrlTimeOut.name: nqaAdminCtrlTimeOut
nqaAdminCtrlTimeOut.description: Specifies the duration to wait for the completion of test instance. The default value of DHCP-type and FTP-type test instance is 15s, The default value of PPPoE-type test instance is 30s, and that of other types is 3s.

nqaAdminCtrlThreshold1.name: nqaAdminCtrlThreshold1
nqaAdminCtrlThreshold1.description: Represents the threshold of RTD (Round Trip Delay). If the RTT violates the threshold, the corresponding counter will increase. It applies to any type of test instance.

nqaAdminCtrlThreshold2.name: nqaAdminCtrlThreshold2
nqaAdminCtrlThreshold2.description: Represents the threshold of OWD (One Way Delay) from source to destination. If the OWD violates the threshold, the corresponding counter will increase. It applies only to jitter-type test instances.

nqaAdminCtrlThreshold3.name: nqaAdminCtrlThreshold3
nqaAdminCtrlThreshold3.description: Represents the threshold of OWD (One Way Delay) from destination to source. If the OWD violates the threshold, the corresponding counter will increase. It applies only to jitter-type test instances.

nqaAdminCtrlStatus.name: nqaAdminCtrlStatus
nqaAdminCtrlStatus.reference: See definition of RowStatus in RFC 2579, 'Textual Conventions for SMIv2.'
nqaAdminCtrlStatus.description: To set the value of this object can create or delete the specified test instance and the records belonging to it. Before deleting a test instance, the custom must make sure that the status of the test instance is inactive through nqaScheduleOperStatus. The value can be set to 'CreateAndGo (4)', 'Destroy (6)' and 'Active (1)'.

nqaAdminParaMaxFailures.name: nqaAdminParaMaxFailures
nqaAdminParaMaxFailures.description: The value of this object indicates the maximum number of consecutive timeouts allowed before terminating a remote traceroute request. A value of 255 (maximum hop count/possible TTL value) indicates that the function of terminating a remote traceroute request when a specific number of successive timeouts are detected is disabled.

nqaAdminParaIfIndex.name: nqaAdminParaIfIndex

nqaAdminParaByPassRouteTable.name: nqaAdminParaByPassRouteTable
nqaAdminParaByPassRouteTable.description: The purpose of this object is to optionally enable bypassing the route table. If enabled, the remote host will bypass the normal routing tables and send directly to a host on an attached network. If the host is not on a directly-attached network, an error is returned. This option can be used to perform the ping/traceroute operation to a local host through an interface that has no route defined (e.g., after the interface was dropped by routed).

nqaAdminParaProbeCount.name: nqaAdminParaProbeCount

nqaAdminParaTrapGeneration.name: nqaAdminParaTrapGeneration
nqaAdminParaTrapGeneration.description: Switch of notification. Determine whether and how to send notifications for the test instance: - probeFailure(0) - Generate a PathChange notification when the current path varies from a previously determined path. - testFailure(1) - Generate a TestFailed notification when the full path to a target can't be determined. - testCompletion(2) - Generate a TestCompleted notification when the path to a target has been determined. - overRtdThreshold(3) - Generate a Overthreshold of RTD notification when the statistic results exceed threshold. - overOwdThresholdSd(4) - Generate a Overthreshold of OWD-SD notification when the statistic results exceed threshold. - overOwdThresholdDs(5) - Generate a Overthreshold of OWD-DS notification when the statistic results exceed threshold. The value #0x00 indicates disable all notifications.

nqaAdminParaTrapProbeFailureFilter.name: nqaAdminParaTrapProbeFailureFilter
nqaAdminParaTrapProbeFailureFilter.description: Specifies the condition when to trigger an nqaProbeFailed notification. When the number of consecutive failed probes violates the threshold indicated by nqaAdminParaTrapProbeFailureFilter, a notification will be created. This object is used together with nqaAdminParaTrapGeneration.

nqaAdminParaTrapTestFailureFilter.name: nqaAdminParaTrapTestFailureFilter
nqaAdminParaTrapTestFailureFilter.description: Specifies the condition when to trigger an nqaTestFailed notification. When the number of failed tests violates the threshold indicated by nqaAdminParaTrapTestFailureFilter, a notification will be created. There are usually several probes in each test. This object is used together with nqaAdminParaTrapGeneration.

nqaScheduleStartType.name: nqaScheduleStartType
nqaScheduleStartType.description: Specifies the start type of the test instance. The object is used together with nqaScheduleStartTime.

nqaScheduleStartTime.name: nqaScheduleStartTime
nqaScheduleStartTime.description: Specifies the start time of the test instance. Setting the value to 0 indicates to start the test instance immediately. After configuring this object, the status of the test instance is active, and the parameters of the test instance can't be changed.

nqaScheduleEndType.name: nqaScheduleEndType
nqaScheduleEndType.description: Specifies the end type of the test instance. The object is used together with nqaScheduleEndTime.

nqaScheduleEndTime.name: nqaScheduleEndTime
nqaScheduleEndTime.description: Specifies the end time of the test instance.

nqaScheduleAgeTime.name: nqaScheduleAgeTime
nqaScheduleAgeTime.description: Specifies the aging time of the test instance, the time how long the test instance will be reserved in NQA, after the test instance is inactive. Setting the value to 0 indicates reserving the test instance eternally.

nqaScheduleElapsedTime.name: nqaScheduleElapsedTime
nqaScheduleElapsedTime.description: The elapsed time (the period of time after task dispatch).

nqaScheduleNumOfInitiations.name: nqaScheduleNumOfInitiations
nqaScheduleNumOfInitiations.description: Specifies the times that the test instance has been initialed. This object is used as the index of the result table, HTTP statistics table, jitter statistics table, FTP statistics table and history table.

nqaScheduleLastFinishIndex.name: nqaScheduleLastFinishIndex
nqaScheduleLastFinishIndex.description: Specifies the latest finished test of the test instance, which is used as the index of the result table.

nqaScheduleOperStatus.name: nqaScheduleOperStatus
nqaScheduleOperStatus.description: Specifies the status of dispatching operation: - reset: Clear all the records of the test instance. - stop: Stop the test instance, if it's running. - restart: Stop the test instance, if it's running, and restart the test instance immediately. - active: The test instance is running; the parameters of the test instances can't be changed. - inactive: The test instance doesn't be scheduled; the parameters of the test instances can be changed.

nqaScheduleLastCollectIndex.name: nqaScheduleLastCollectIndex
nqaScheduleLastCollectIndex.description: Specifies the index of the latest collection statistics result record in the collection result table.

nqaGroupStatusType.name: nqaGroupStatusType
nqaGroupStatusType.description: Specifies the group status of the test instance. The value can be normal (1), leader (2) or member (3).

nqaGroupPeriod.name: nqaGroupPeriod
nqaGroupPeriod.description: Specifies the interval during which all members in the specified group will be executed.

nqaGroupLeaderOwnerIndex.name: nqaGroupLeaderOwnerIndex
nqaGroupLeaderOwnerIndex.description: Specifies the owner index of the group leader, if the test instance is a member of the group.

nqaGroupLeaderTestName.name: nqaGroupLeaderTestName
nqaGroupLeaderTestName.description: Specifies the test name of the group leader, if the test instance is a member of the group.

nqaGroupMemberNum.name: nqaGroupMemberNum
nqaGroupMemberNum.description: Specifies the number of member in the group.

nqaGroupMemberFree.name: nqaGroupMemberFree
nqaGroupMemberFree.description: Free all members in the group.

nqaServerEnable.name: nqaServerEnable
nqaServerEnable.description: Enables NQA server, which can be the echo server of TCP, UDP and jitter type test instance.

nqaTcpServerTable.name: nqaTcpServerTable
nqaTcpServerTable.description: A table which contains the status of nqa tcp server configuration information.

nqaTcpServerEntry.name: nqaTcpServerEntry
nqaTcpServerEntry.description: A table which contains the status of nqa tcp server configuration information. This entry is included not only the tcp server ip address but also the tcp server tcp port. If used for VPN it is also included the VPN name.

nqaTcpServerAddressType.name: nqaTcpServerAddressType
nqaTcpServerAddressType.description: Specifies the address type of TCP server.

nqaTcpServerAddress.name: nqaTcpServerAddress
nqaTcpServerAddress.description: Specifies the address of TCP server.

nqaTcpServerPort.name: nqaTcpServerPort
nqaTcpServerPort.description: Specifies the port number on which TCP server is listening.

nqaTcpServerVrfName.name: nqaTcpServerVrfName
nqaTcpServerVrfName.description: Specifies the VRF (VPN Routing & Forwarding) instances name of the TCP server.

nqaTcpServerStatus.name: nqaTcpServerStatus
nqaTcpServerStatus.reference: See definition of RowStatus in RFC 2579, 'Textual Conventions for SMIv2.'
nqaTcpServerStatus.description: Specifies the operation of the TCP server, creating or deleting.

nqaUdpServerTable.name: nqaUdpServerTable
nqaUdpServerTable.description: A table which contains the status of nqa udp server configuration information.

nqaUdpServerEntry.name: nqaUdpServerEntry
nqaUdpServerEntry.description: A table which contains the status of nqa udp server configuration information. This entry is includeed not only the udp server ip address but also the udp server udp port.If used for VPN it is also included the VPN name.

nqaUdpServerAddressType.name: nqaUdpServerAddressType
nqaUdpServerAddressType.description: Specifies the address type of UDP server.

nqaUdpServerAddress.name: nqaUdpServerAddress
nqaUdpServerAddress.description: Specifies the address of UDP server.

nqaUdpServerPort.name: nqaUdpServerPort
nqaUdpServerPort.description: Specifies the port number on which UDP server is listening.

nqaUdpServerVrfName.name: nqaUdpServerVrfName
nqaUdpServerVrfName.description: Specifies the VRF (VPN Routing & Forwarding) instances name of the UDP server.

nqaUdpServerStatus.name: nqaUdpServerStatus
nqaUdpServerStatus.reference: See definition of RowStatus in RFC 2579, 'Textual Conventions for SMIv2.'
nqaUdpServerStatus.description: Specifies the operation of the UDP server, creating or deleting.

nqaIcmpServerTable.name: nqaIcmpServerTable
nqaIcmpServerTable.description: A table which contains the status of nqa ICMP server configuration information.

nqaIcmpServerEntry.name: nqaIcmpServerEntry
nqaIcmpServerEntry.description: A table which contains the status of nqa ICMP server configuration information. This entry is included the ICMP server IP address. If used for VPN it is also included the VPN name.

nqaIcmpServerAddress.name: nqaIcmpServerAddress
nqaIcmpServerAddress.description: Specifies the address of ICMP server.

nqaIcmpServerVrfName.name: nqaIcmpServerVrfName
nqaIcmpServerVrfName.description: Specifies the VRF (VPN Routing & Forwarding) instances name of the ICMP server.

nqaIcmpServerAddressType.name: nqaIcmpServerAddressType
nqaIcmpServerAddressType.description: Specifies the address type of ICMP server.

nqaIcmpServerStatus.name: nqaIcmpServerStatus
nqaIcmpServerStatus.reference: See definition of RowStatus in RFC 2579, 'Textual Conventions for SMIv2.'
nqaIcmpServerStatus.description: Specifies the operation of the ICMP server, creating or deleting.

nqaResultsTable.name: nqaResultsTable
nqaResultsTable.description: Defines the test Results Extend Table for providing the capability of performing test operations at a remote host. The results of these operations are stored in the nqaResultsTable . The operation of this table is same as that of nqaResultsTable.

nqaResultsEntry.name: nqaResultsEntry
nqaResultsEntry.description: The operation of this table is same as that of nqaResultsTable.

nqaResultsIndex.name: nqaResultsIndex
nqaResultsIndex.description: The result table index and times of dispatching dependency tests. Each test can only reserve 5 records. The result table only contains icmp/dns/dlsw/lspPing/Traceroute/LSP Traceroute/tcp/udp/snmp/dhcp Traceroute information.

nqaResultsHopIndex.name: nqaResultsHopIndex
nqaResultsHopIndex.description: The hop index. If the test type is Traceroute or LSP Traceroute, the entry only defines one hop. For other types, the default value is 1.

nqaResultsTestAttempts.name: nqaResultsTestAttempts
nqaResultsTestAttempts.description: The times of executing tests, which includes the times of successful execution, failed execution and interruption (interrupted by human or system). The current number of test attempts. The value of this object MUST be started at 0.

nqaResultsCurHopCount.name: nqaResultsCurHopCount
nqaResultsCurHopCount.description: It is equal to the hop count index executed by current Traceroute or LSP Traceroute tests. Ping/LSP Ping does not use this entry. The default value is 0.

nqaResultsCurProbeCount.name: nqaResultsCurProbeCount
nqaResultsCurProbeCount.description: The total count of probe packets of Traceroute or LSP Traceroute test in a hop count index.

nqaResultsRTDOverThresholds.name: nqaResultsRTDOverThresholds
nqaResultsRTDOverThresholds.description: The times of successful statistics test RTD (Round Trip Delay) over the threshold.

nqaResultsSumCompletionTime.name: nqaResultsSumCompletionTime
nqaResultsSumCompletionTime.description: The sum of RTT (response time) of all packets of each hop for executing Traceroute, LSP Traceroute tests. The sum of RTT (response time) of sent packets for executing ping, lsp ping and disman-ping tests and so on.

nqaResultsSumCompletionTime2Low.name: nqaResultsSumCompletionTime2Low
nqaResultsSumCompletionTime2Low.description: The low order 32 bits of the accumulated squares of completion times (in milliseconds) of NQA operations which complete successfully. Low/High order is defined where the binary number will look as follows: ------------------------------------------------- | High order 32 bits | Low order 32 bits | ------------------------------------------------- For example the number 4294967296 would have all Low order bits as '0' and the rightmost High order bit will be 1 (zeros,1).

nqaResultsSumCompletionTime2High.name: nqaResultsSumCompletionTime2High
nqaResultsSumCompletionTime2High.description: The high order 32 bits of the accumulated squares of completion times (in milliseconds) of NQA operations which complete successfully. See the nqaResultsSumCompletionTime2Low object for a definition of Low/High Order.

nqaResultsCompletionTimeMin.name: nqaResultsCompletionTimeMin
nqaResultsCompletionTimeMin.description: The minimum RTT (for Traceroute and LSP Traceroute, it is the minimum RTT among all the packet of next hop) of all packets for executing a test.

nqaResultsCompletionTimeMax.name: nqaResultsCompletionTimeMax
nqaResultsCompletionTimeMax.description: The maximum RTT (for Traceroute and LSP Traceroute, it is the maximum RTT among all the packets of next hop) of all packets in executing a test.

nqaResultsDisconnects.name: nqaResultsDisconnects
nqaResultsDisconnects.description: The times of consecutive failures. For connectionless protocol type of test,this number should be zero.

nqaResultsTimeouts.name: nqaResultsTimeouts
nqaResultsTimeouts.description: The number of occasions when a NQA operation was not completed before a timeout occurred, i.e. nqaAdminCtrlTimeOut was exceeded.

nqaResultsBusies.name: nqaResultsBusies
nqaResultsBusies.description: The times of failure to apply resource due to the busy system. such as apply memory or create socket failure.

nqaResultsNoConnections.name: nqaResultsNoConnections
nqaResultsNoConnections.description: The number of occasions when a NQA operation could not be initiated because the connection to the target has not been established. For all other nqaAdminCtrlType this object will remain zero. This cannot occur for connectionless protocols, but may occur for connection oriented protocols, such as TCP. Since a NQA operation was never initiated, the completion time of these operations are not accumulated, nor do they increment nqaResultsCompletions.

nqaResultsSequenceErrors.name: nqaResultsSequenceErrors
nqaResultsSequenceErrors.description: The number of NQA operation completions received with an unexpected sequence identifier. For all other values of nqaAdminCtrlType this object will remain zero. When this has occurred some of the possible reasons maybe: - a duplicate packet was received - a response was received after it had timed-out - a corrupted packet was received and was not detected

nqaResultsDrops.name: nqaResultsDrops
nqaResultsDrops.description: The times probes of the test dropped due to sending or connecting failure.

nqaResultsAddressType.name: nqaResultsAddressType
nqaResultsAddressType.description: The destination address type, and the value range can be unknown(0), ipv4(1) and dns(16).

nqaResultsAddress.name: nqaResultsAddress
nqaResultsAddress.description: The destination address (TraceRoute is the destination address of each hop, and ping is the destination address of tests).

nqaResultsProbeResponses.name: nqaResultsProbeResponses
nqaResultsProbeResponses.description: Number of responses received for the corresponding test. The value of this object MUST be reported as 0 when no probe responses have been received.

nqaResultsSentProbes.name: nqaResultsSentProbes
nqaResultsSentProbes.description: The value of this object reflects the number of probes sent for the corresponding test. The value of this object MUST be reported as 0 when no probes have been sent.

nqaResultsLastGoodProbe.name: nqaResultsLastGoodProbe
nqaResultsLastGoodProbe.description: Date and time when the last response was received for a probe.

nqaResultsLastGoodPath.name: nqaResultsLastGoodPath
nqaResultsLastGoodPath.description: The date and time when the last complete path was determined.

nqaResultsRttAvg.name: nqaResultsRttAvg
nqaResultsRttAvg.description: The average of RTTs that were successfully measured by tests.

nqaResultsLostPacketRatio.name: nqaResultsLostPacketRatio
nqaResultsLostPacketRatio.description: The ratio of the packets lost to all packets sent in the test.

nqaHTTPStatsTable.name: nqaHTTPStatsTable
nqaHTTPStatsTable.description: The statistics collection database. Defines the HTTP Operations Statistics Table for storing the statistics of a HTTP test.

nqaHTTPStatsEntry.name: nqaHTTPStatsEntry
nqaHTTPStatsEntry.description: Defines an entry in the nqaHTTPStatsTable.

nqaHTTPStatsIndex.name: nqaHTTPStatsIndex
nqaHTTPStatsIndex.description: The The HTTP statistics table index and times of dispatching dependency tests.

nqaHTTPStatsRTDOverThresholds.name: nqaHTTPStatsRTDOverThresholds
nqaHTTPStatsRTDOverThresholds.description: The number of HTTP operations RTD (Round Trip Delay) that violate threshold.

nqaHTTPStatsRTTSum.name: nqaHTTPStatsRTTSum
nqaHTTPStatsRTTSum.description: The sum of delay time of successful HTTP probes, including the sum of time of DNS query, TCP establishment and packets transmission.

nqaHTTPStatsRTTMin.name: nqaHTTPStatsRTTMin
nqaHTTPStatsRTTMin.description: The minimum value of HTTP probe time.

nqaHTTPStatsRTTMax.name: nqaHTTPStatsRTTMax
nqaHTTPStatsRTTMax.description: The maximum value of HTTP probe time.

nqaHTTPStatsDNSRTTSum.name: nqaHTTPStatsDNSRTTSum
nqaHTTPStatsDNSRTTSum.description: The sum of DNS query time.

nqaHTTPStatsDNSRTTMin.name: nqaHTTPStatsDNSRTTMin
nqaHTTPStatsDNSRTTMin.description: The minimum of DNS query time.

nqaHTTPStatsDNSRTTMax.name: nqaHTTPStatsDNSRTTMax
nqaHTTPStatsDNSRTTMax.description: The maximum of DNS query time.

nqaHTTPStatsTCPConnectRTTSum.name: nqaHTTPStatsTCPConnectRTTSum
nqaHTTPStatsTCPConnectRTTSum.description: The sum of TCP connection time.

nqaHTTPStatsTCPConnectRTTMin.name: nqaHTTPStatsTCPConnectRTTMin
nqaHTTPStatsTCPConnectRTTMin.description: The minimum value of TCP connection time.

nqaHTTPStatsTCPConnectRTTMax.name: nqaHTTPStatsTCPConnectRTTMax
nqaHTTPStatsTCPConnectRTTMax.description: The maximum value of TCP connection time.

nqaHTTPStatsTransactionRTTMin.name: nqaHTTPStatsTransactionRTTMin
nqaHTTPStatsTransactionRTTMin.description: The minimum value of transaction time.

nqaHTTPStatsTransactionRTTMax.name: nqaHTTPStatsTransactionRTTMax
nqaHTTPStatsTransactionRTTMax.description: The maximum value of transaction time.

nqaHTTPStatsMessageBodyOctetsSum.name: nqaHTTPStatsMessageBodyOctetsSum
nqaHTTPStatsMessageBodyOctetsSum.description: The sum of the size of the message body received as a response to the HTTP request.

nqaHTTPStatsDNSServerTimeouts.name: nqaHTTPStatsDNSServerTimeouts
nqaHTTPStatsDNSServerTimeouts.description: The number of requests that timed out during DNS query.

nqaHTTPStatsTCPConnectTimeouts.name: nqaHTTPStatsTCPConnectTimeouts
nqaHTTPStatsTCPConnectTimeouts.description: The number of requests that timed out during HTTP connection.

nqaHTTPStatsTransactionTimeouts.name: nqaHTTPStatsTransactionTimeouts
nqaHTTPStatsTransactionTimeouts.description: The number of requests that timed out during HTTP transaction.

nqaHTTPStatsDNSQueryErrors.name: nqaHTTPStatsDNSQueryErrors
nqaHTTPStatsDNSQueryErrors.description: The number of requests that had DNS query errors.

nqaHTTPStatsErrors.name: nqaHTTPStatsErrors
nqaHTTPStatsErrors.description: The number of HTTP transaction failures.

nqaHTTPStatsTcpConnErrors.name: nqaHTTPStatsTcpConnErrors
nqaHTTPStatsTcpConnErrors.description: The number of TCP connection failures.

nqaHTTPStatsProbeResponses.name: nqaHTTPStatsProbeResponses
nqaHTTPStatsProbeResponses.description: Number of responses received for the corresponding test. The value of this object MUST be reported as 0 when no probe responses have been received.

nqaHTTPStatsBusies.name: nqaHTTPStatsBusies
nqaHTTPStatsBusies.description: The number of occasions when a HTTP operation could not be initiated because an internal error.

nqaHTTPStatsRttAvg.name: nqaHTTPStatsRttAvg
nqaHTTPStatsRttAvg.description: The average of RTTs that were successfully measured by tests.

nqaHTTPStatsLostPacketRatio.name: nqaHTTPStatsLostPacketRatio
nqaHTTPStatsLostPacketRatio.description: The ratio of the packets lost to all packets sent in the test.

nqaJitterStatsTable.name: nqaJitterStatsTable
nqaJitterStatsTable.description: A table which contains the status of latest Jitter operation.

nqaJitterStatsEntry.name: nqaJitterStatsEntry
nqaJitterStatsEntry.description: A table which contains the status of latest Jitter operation. This entry is created only if the nqaAdminCtrlType is jitterAppl.

nqaJitterStatsIndex.name: nqaJitterStatsIndex
nqaJitterStatsIndex.description: The third index of jitter statistics table.

nqaJitterStatsCompletions.name: nqaJitterStatsCompletions
nqaJitterStatsCompletions.description: The result of the test, which value can be noResult (0), success (1), failure (2) or negotiateFailed (3). If the test is still running, the value will be noResult (0).

nqaJitterStatsRTDOverThresholds.name: nqaJitterStatsRTDOverThresholds
nqaJitterStatsRTDOverThresholds.description: The number of tests that violate RTD (Round Trip Delay) threshold.

nqaJitterStatsNumOfRTT.name: nqaJitterStatsNumOfRTT
nqaJitterStatsNumOfRTT.description: The number of RTTs that are successfully measured by tests.

nqaJitterStatsRTTSum.name: nqaJitterStatsRTTSum
nqaJitterStatsRTTSum.description: The sum of RTTs that are successfully measured.

nqaJitterStatsRTTSum2Low.name: nqaJitterStatsRTTSum2Low
nqaJitterStatsRTTSum2Low.description: The sum of squares of RTTs that are successfully measured by tests (low order 32 bits).

nqaJitterStatsRTTSum2High.name: nqaJitterStatsRTTSum2High
nqaJitterStatsRTTSum2High.description: The sum of squares of RTTs that are successfully measured by tests (high order 32 bits).

nqaJitterStatsRTTMin.name: nqaJitterStatsRTTMin
nqaJitterStatsRTTMin.description: The minimum of RTTs that were successfully measured by tests.

nqaJitterStatsRTTMax.name: nqaJitterStatsRTTMax

nqaMtracertHistoryFwdCode.name: nqaMtracertHistoryFwdCode
nqaMtracertHistoryFwdCode.description: This field contains a forwarding information/error code. noError(1): No error wrongIf(2): Traceroute request arrived on an interface to which this router would not forward for this source,group,destination. pruneSent(3): This router has sent a prune upstream which applies to the source and group in the tracer- oute request. pruneRCVD(4): This router has stopped forwarding for this source and group in response to a request from the next hop router. scoped(5): The group is subject to administrative scoping at this hop. noRoute(6): This router has no route for the source or group and no way to determine a potential route. wrongLastHop(7): This router is not the proper last-hop router. notForwarding(8):This router is not forwarding this source,group out the outgoing interface for an unspecified reason. reachedRP(9): Reached Rendez-vous Point or Core rpfIf(10): Traceroute request arrived on the expected RPF interface for this source,group. noMulticast(11): Traceroute request arrived on an interface which is not enabled for multicast. infoHidden(12): One or more hops have been hidden from this trace. noSpace(13): There was not enough room to insert another response data block in the packet. oldRouter(14): The previous hop router does not understand traceroute requests. adminProhib(15): Traceroute is administratively prohibited.
